  "prompt": "Where online can I use my Maestro card?",
  "response": "Maestro cards are generally accepted at a wide range of online merchants, but acceptance can vary depending on the merchant and your specific country. Some major online platforms and e-commerce stores that may accept Maestro cards include:\n\n1. **Amazon**: Depending on the region, Amazon may accept Maestro cards for payment.\n2. **eBay**: Many sellers on eBay accept Maestro cards.\n3. **Booking.com**: If you're booking travel accommodations, Booking.com often accepts a variety of payment methods, including Maestro.\n4. **Asos**: This popular online fashion retailer may accept Maestro cards.\n5. **Airbnb**: Sometimes you can use Maestro cards to book accommodations.\n6. **Uber**: Uber typically accepts Maestro cards for rides and Uber Eats orders in some regions.\n7. **Digital Wallets**: You can add your Maestro card to digital wallets like PayPal or Google Pay and use it for transactions on sites that accept these wallets.\n\nIt's important to check out the specific merchant's payment options and see if Maestro is listed as a method. Additionally, you can always contact customer support of the online store you wish to purchase from to confirm whether they accept Maestro cards.",
